income-tax-rates\" title=\"Income Tax rates\">limit for an age-related allowance</a></li>\n  <li>have lived or worked abroad or you aren&rsquo;t <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/international/personal.htm\" title=\"Residence\">domiciled in the UK</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Check with <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> if you don’t think you have to send a tax return.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Self Assessment Helpline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>0845 900 0444<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 8am to 4pm</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/self-assessment-tax-returns/deadlines","slug":"deadlines","order":3,"title":"Deadlines","body":"<h2>Filing your tax return</h2>\n\n<p>The 2011 to 2012 tax year ended 5 April 2012. The main deadlines are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>paper tax returns - midnight 31 October 2012</li>\n  <li>online tax returns - midnight 31 January 2013</li>\n  <li>final payment of any tax due - midnight 31 January 2013</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you’ve missed the paper deadline, <a href=\"/file-your-self-assessment-tax-return\" title=\"Login and file your Self Assessment tax return\">send your return online</a> instead to avoid a penalty.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Exceptions</h3>\n\n<p>The deadline for sending the tax return can be different.   </p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong><br />\nDeadline: 30 December - if you send your return online, owe less than £3,000, and want HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) to try and collect the tax through your tax code.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong><br />\nDeadline: 31 January - if you&rsquo;re a trustee of a registered pension scheme or a non-resident company (you must send a paper return because you can&rsquo;t do it online).</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"exam