a hearing</h2>\n\n<p>Make sure you bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the &lsquo;statement of case&rsquo;, if you&rsquo;ve been sent one (this is a legal document <abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will send you unless the case is basic)</li>\n  <li>your response to the statement of case (this includes factual evidence and a list of the documents you&rsquo;ll be relying on in the hearing)</li>\n  <li>any other documents you&rsquo;ll be relying on - eg invoices, accounts or bank statements</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Send copies of the documents to <abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> and the tribunal at least 14 days before the hearing.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Who will be at a hearing</h2>\n\n<p>The hearing will be attended by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a tribunal panel - which can include a tribunal judge and expert members</li>\n  <li>a tribunal clerk</li>\n  <li>a representative from the department/agency (eg <abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>any witnesses</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can bring a representative and a friend, family member or colleague.</p>\n\n<h2>What happens at a hearing</h2>\n\n<p>You or your representative will normally put your case first, saying why you think the decision is wrong and giving facts to support your argument.</p>\n\n<p>The department&rsquo;s or agency&rsquo;s representative will then present the case for the other side.</p>\n\n<p>The tribunal may also ask questions during the hearing.</p>\n\n<p>You can find out more about what happens at a hearing in the booklet below:</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/tribunals/tax/forms-and-how-to-appeal/at-your-hearing.pdf\" title=\"Download 'At your tax tribunal hearing' (PDF, 92KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘At your tax tribunal hearing’ (PDF, 92KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Getting the decision</h2>\n\n<p>The tribunal may tell you the decision on the day of the hearing.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll get a letter giving you the decision in writing.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tax-tribunal/if-you-lose-your-case","slug":"if-you-lose-your-case","order":4,"title":"If you lose your case","body":"<p>If you lose your case, ask the tribunal for a copy of the full written decision.</p>\n\n<h2>Ask the tribunal to look at a case again</h2>\n\n<p>You can ask the tribunal to look at the case again if there was something wrong with the way it was handled, eg:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you didn&rsquo;t receive paperwork about the case</li>\n  <li>someone didn&rsquo;t turn up for your hearing</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Ask for permission to appeal</h2>\n\n<p>You may be able to appeal against the decision if the tribunal made a legal mistake, eg it didn&rsquo;t:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>apply the law correctly</li>\n  <li>give good reasons for its decision</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>To ask for permission to appeal, use the form below:</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/forms/tribunals/tax/appeal-upper-tribunal-form.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Application for permission to appeal to Upper Tribunal (Tax and Chancery) Chamber' (PDF, 35KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application for permission to appeal to Upper Tribunal (Tax and Chancery) Chamber’ (PDF, 35KB)</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/forms/tribunals/tax/appeal-upper-tribunal-form.doc\" title=\"Download 'Application for permission to appeal to Upper Tribunal (Tax and Chancery) Chamber' (DOC, 124KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application for permission to appeal to Upper Tribunal (Tax and Chancery) Chamber’ (DOC, 124KB)</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/tribunals/tax/forms-and-how-to-appeal/appealing-upper-tribunal-form-completion-guide.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Guidance on applying for permission to appeal to Upper Tribunal (Tax and Chancery) Chamber' (PDF, 37KB)\" rel=\"externa