r title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> has <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/vat/managing/reclaiming/index.htm\" title=\"Reclaim VAT\">guidance on these exceptions</a> and working out how to reclaim <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> for: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>cars - eg buying, repairing, fuel costs</li>\n  <li>staff travel expenses - eg accommodation and transport expenses </li>\n  <li>reclaiming <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> if your business is partly exempt from <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Estimated figures</h2>\n\n<p>If you can&rsquo;t give accurate figures on your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return, <a href=\"/vat-helpline\" title=\"VAT Helpline\">ask <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> for permission</a> to use estimated figures.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re allowed, you won&rsquo;t be charged a penalty unless you miss the deadline or make a careless or deliberate error. </p>\n\n<h2>Bad debts</h2>\n\n<p>You can reclaim the <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> you&rsquo;ve paid <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> but not received from a customer if it&rsquo;s a &lsquo;bad debt&rsquo; (one you&rsquo;ve written off). To qualify for the relief:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the debt must be between 6 months and 4 years and 6 months old </li>\n  <li>you mustn&rsquo;t have sold the debt on </li>\n  <li>you mustn&rsquo;t have charged more than the normal price for the item</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You should reclaim them via your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return (add them to your Box 4 figure) and <a href=\"/vat-record-keeping/vat-account\" title=\"VAT record keeping\">keep records</a> about the debt.</p>\n\n<p>If the debt is paid, you must pay the relief back via your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return (add the amount to your Box 1 figure). </p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/vat-returns/send-your-return","slug":"send