of the unpaid tax. <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> estimate this if they don&rsquo;t have your return - this is known as an <a href=\"/vat-returns/assessments\" title=\"VAT assessments\">&lsquo;assessment&rsquo;</a>.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Default</th>\n      <th>Penalty if turnover is less than £150,000</th>\n      <th>Penalty if turnover is  £150,000 or more</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>1st</td>\n      <td>No penalty but if you default again within 12 months you enter a surcharge period</td>\n      <td>No penalty but you enter a surcharge period</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>2nd</td>\n      <td>No penalty</td>\n      <td>2% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>3rd</td>\n      <td>2% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n      <td>5% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>4th</td>\n      <td>5% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n      <td>10%</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>5th</td>\n      <td>10%</td>\n      <td>15%</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>6 or more</td>\n      <td>15%</td>\n      <td>15%</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Exceptions</h3>\n\n<p>There’s no penalty if you send a late <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return and you have no tax to pay or you’re due a <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> repayment. </p>\n\n<h2>Penalties for incorrect <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Returns</h2>\n\n<p>If your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return is inaccurate <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> can charge you a penalty (between 15% and 100% of the unpaid owed). </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/about/new-penalties/new-penalties.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Penalties for inaccurate tax returns' (PDF, 200KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Penalties for inaccurate tax ret