ww.hmrc.gov.uk/vat/start/register/how-to-register.htm\" title=\"Registering for VAT by post\">register by post</a> if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you want to apply for a ‘<a href=\"/vat-registration/when-to-register\" title=\"Exceptions to compulsory VAT registration\">registration exception</a>’ </li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re an EU business ‘distance selling’ to the UK </li>\n  <li>you import (‘acquire’) goods from another EU country </li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re registering for <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> and joining the Agricultural Flat Rate Scheme</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re registering the divisions or business units of a body corporate under separate <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> numbers</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re disposing of assets on which 8th or 13th Directive refunds have been claimed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you register by post, you must <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://online.hmrc.gov.uk/registration/organisation\" title=\"Sign up for a VAT online account\">sign up for an <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> online account</a>\n separately (select option &lsquo;<abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> submit returns&rsquo;). You can only do this <strong>after</strong> <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> sends your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> number to you.  </p>\n\n<h2>How long does it take?</h2>\n\n<p>You should get a <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> registration certificate within 30 working days, though it can take longer. </p>\n\n<p>It’s sent to your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> online account (or in the post if an agent registers you or you can&rsquo;t register online). </p>\n\n<h2>What you need to know</h2>\n\n<p>You need to provide details like your turnover, business activity and bank details.  </p>\n\n<p>Your registration date is known as your &lsquo;effective date of registration&rsquo;. You must pay <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> the <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> due from this date.</p>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t need to authorise an agent to register you for <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr>.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/vat-registration/when-to-register","slug":"when-to-register","order":3,"title":"When to register","body":"<p>You must register when you go over the threshold, or know that you will. The threshold is based on your estimated <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/vat/start/register/when-to-register.htm#6\" title=\"Calculate your VAT taxable turnover\"><abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> taxable turnover</a> - the total of everything sold that isn&rsquo;t <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> exempt. </p>\n\n<h2>Compulsory registration</h2>\n\n<p>You must register for <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your estimated <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> taxable turnover is more than £77,000 (the &lsquo;threshold&rsquo;) in a 12 month period</li>\n  <li>you receive goods in the UK from the EU worth more than £77,000  </li>\n  <li>you expect to go over the threshold in a single 30 day period </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"/vat-registration-thresholds\" title=\"VAT registration thresholds\">threshold is different</a> if you supply goods and services to the UK from abroad. </p>\n\n<p>If you register late, HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) can charge you a penalty (between 5% and 15% of the <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> you owe). </p>\n\n<h2>Voluntary registration</h2>\n\n<p>You can register voluntarily if your business turnover is below £77,000. You must pay <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> the <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> you owe from the date they register you. </p>\n\n<h2>Get an exception</h2>\n\n<p>You can apply for a &lsquo;registration exception&rsquo; (eg because your turnover goes over the threshold temporarily). 